Liquid    Spill

Step 1: Triage Unit

Step 2: Perform part swaps (except keyboard) as needed to repair

Step 3: Put unit on Hold for Management, summarizing what unit needs. If Liquid was found and the unit has a problem, take detailed close ups of the spills and email to pictures@microreplay.com

Step 4: Once Unit is approved, or in some cases denied, complete process and test.

Liquid    Spill

Whole Unit Repair

Step 1: Triage Unit

Step 2: Perform necessary repairs as expected, whether part swaps or logic board repairs (often for GPU), and test

Step 3: Refresh unit, remove dust and clean heatsink, fresh thermal paste, and clean screen

Step 4: Send unit to audit (GPU testing requires overnight burn-in first)

Liquid    Spill

LCD Replacement

Step 1: Triage Unit

Step 2: Remove old clamshell, if confirmed damaged

Step 3: Replace with repaired LCD or replacement clamshell, and test unit

Step 4: Send to audit
